      <div class="project-three">
         <img src="/images/erp.png" alt="" srcset="">
        <h1>ERP platform (Front-End Developer Intern)</h1>
        <div class="tools">
          <h2>Tools:</h2>
          <p>Back-End - Django Rest Framework</p>
          <p>Front-End - ReactJS</p>
          <p>Database - PostgreSQL</p>
        </div>
      
        <div class="func">
          <h2>Created functionalities:</h2>
          <p>-Created product, supplier, login, register,profile page and
            authentication protocols such as JWT and OAuth2 to protect sensitive
            data and ensure secure access.</p>
          <p>-Collaborated with back-end developers to integrate system
            interactions, utilizing Python for data handling and API
            communication.</p>
          <p>-Implemented responsive design and optimized the user interface for
            better performance and usability.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="project">
        <h1>Real estate site (study case)</h1>
        <div class="tools">
          <h2>Tools:</h2>
          <p>Back-End - interfacing with the SoftUni Practice Server</p>
          <p>Front-End - ReactJS</p>
        </div>
        <div class="func">
          <h2>Created functionalities:</h2>
          <p>The project boasts a structured component architecture, utilizing
            React Router for seamless navigation and CSS for styling.</p>
          <p>- Key features include user authentication with secure
            registration/login/logout, property management (create, edit,
            delete), and a comments system.</p>
          <p>- The contact page integrates Google Maps for location
            visualization and a form to submit questions.</p>
          <p>- Technologies used include ReactJS, SoftUni Practice Server, CSS,
            React Router, react-toastify for notifications, Leaflet for map
            integration and form validation.
          </p>
          <p>For more information:<a
              href="https://github.com/EmineSelimovska/ReactJS-Project"
            > <ion-icon name="logo-github"></ion-icon></a></p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="project-two">
        <h1>E-commerce pizza ordering site (study case)</h1>
        <div class="tools">
          <h2>Tools:</h2>
          <p>Back-End - NodeJS, Express</p>
          <p>Front-End - Angular</p>
          <p>Database - MongoDB</p>
        </div>
        <div class="func">
          <h2>Created functionalities:</h2>
          <p>- Choose to add a product to your cart</p>
          <p>- Select a quantity and proceed to checkout by entering a location
            with Google Maps and then using PayPal for payment. When payment is
            complete, an order details page will appear;</p>
          <p>- For login and registration, there is a validation of the fields
            and for an invalid page it redirects to the"Not Found" page;
          </p>
          <p>- Evaluation is done with ngBootstrap and popups with Toastr.
            Search for a product by name and there are tags by which it is
            possible to sort the products.</p>
          <p>For more information:
            <a
              href="https://github.com/EmineSelimovska/angular-project-express-pizza"
            ><ion-icon name="logo-github"></ion-icon></a></p>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

